OL,3,CMinister facing prospect of jail over
OL,4,C#10k church fraud
OL,6,FDescribing how the convicted thief,
OL,7,F"may well have giveth but he also
OL,8,Fcertainly taketh away," prosecuting
OL,9,Fcounsel Joseph Murphy had highlighted
OL,10,Fto the jury that as rector, the
OL,11,Fdefendant "knew full well" there was
OL,12,Fno treasurer in the church at the time
OL,13,Fand with "hundreds of thousands of
OL,14,Fpounds" going through a building fund
OL,15,Fto rebuild the church after it was
OL,16,Fdecimated in a fire, "he thought sure
OL,17,Fwho is going to notice a measly
OL,18,F#10,000?".
