OL,6,FOn Monday the jury had found him
OL,7,Funanimously guilty of a similar
OL,8,Foffence of fraud by abuse of position
OL,9,Fby taking a #1,000 donation from a
OL,10,Fgrieving widow to line his own pockets
OL,11,Fin that similarly to the first count,
OL,12,Fhe "failed to give or declare the said
OL,13,Fdonation to the treasurer of Church
OL,14,FVestry and made the cheque payable to
OL,15,Fyourself personally".
OL,17,FThe minister was found unanimously not
OL,18,Fguilty of four further fraud offences
OL,19,Frelating to other donations, funeral
OL,20,Fcollections and money obtained through
OL,21,Fa weekly Slimming World class.
